value.value: Catalysis of the sequential cleavage of mononucleotides from a free 5' or 3' terminus of a DNA molecule.

definition.value: Note that the inclusion of 'MetaCyc:BGALACT-PWY' is exceptional: normally MetaCyc pathway entries are database references for biological process terms, not molecular function terms. An exception was made in this case because the MetaCyc entry 'BGALACT-PWY' describes only one reaction, that catalyzed by beta-galactosidase.
